The Levenberg-Marquardt (LM) algorithm is one of the most standard optimization methods used in the NN area (Press et al., 1992; Ampazis and Perantonis, 2000; Hagan and Menhaj, 1994). The LM is a sort of compromise between an offline version of the GD algorithm and a GN method (Marquardt, 1963; Press et al., 1992). The algorithm was introduced for training RNN in (Basterrech et al., 2011).
